# Project Tehuti

"To use Tehuti is to stop programming and start decreeing. You do not debug; you restore order."

A Kimi-style CLI agent, reimagined as Thoth (Tehuti), with OpenRouter-first LLM integration and a ceremonial interface.

## Structure
-  app wiring and lifecycle
-  provider clients and LLM adapters
-  config and persistence
-  terminal UX
-  shared helpers

## Structure
- `src/tehuti_cli/core/` app wiring and lifecycle
- `src/tehuti_cli/providers/` provider clients and LLM adapters
- `src/tehuti_cli/storage/` config and persistence
- `src/tehuti_cli/ui/` terminal UX
- `src/tehuti_cli/utils/` shared helpers

## Commands
- `tehuti` interactive shell
- `tehuti --print -p "..."` print mode
- `tehuti web` minimal web UI
- `tehuti wire` stdio JSON-lines
- `tehuti acp` ACP-compatible alias of wire
